Note: ===================================================================
Note: PARSER STATE
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parser carries the upstream lexer and two slots of lookahead. LL(2) is
necessary because several MATLAB constructs ('identifier (' vs 'identifier['
function-call/indexing dispatch, transpose vs char-array literal
disambiguation) require seeing the byte beyond the current token before
committing to a parse path.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MATLABParser":
    lexer as Integer
    current_token as Integer
    peek_token as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Generic four-field AST node — type tag (NODE_* constants from this file),
payload value (string for identifiers/literals, integer for operator codes),
ordered child list, and a metadata list used by specific node kinds for
function signatures (inputs/outputs separation), classdef inheritance lists,
and other auxiliary data that does not fit cleanly into children.
@End Reasoning
Type called "ASTNode":
    node_type as Integer
    value as Integer
    children as Integer
    metadata as Integer
End Type

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PARSER INITIALIZATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Primes both lookahead slots by pulling two tokens from the lexer at
construction. After this returns, current_token is the first source token
and peek_token is the second; both LL(2) decisions in the parser can fire
from the first call.
@End Reasoning
Process called "matlab_parser_create" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let parser be a value of type MATLABParser with
        lexer as lexer,
        current_token as 0,
        peek_token as 0

    Note: Initialize current and peek tokens
    Set parser.current_token to proc matlab_lexer_next_token from Lexer with lexer
    Set parser.peek_token to proc matlab_lexer_next_token from Lexer with lexer

    Return parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
AST node factory. Initializes value to empty string (the default payload),
and pre-allocates empty children and metadata lists so callers can append
without nullness checks. Every node-emitting helper goes through this so
the layout is consistent.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_ast_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be a value of type ASTNode with
        node_type as node_type,
        value as "",
        children as proc list_create from ListCore,
        metadata as proc list_create from ListCore

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Mutator for the AST node's value payload. Used after create_ast_node when
the node's type-tag-specific payload is determined (e.g. identifier name,
literal text, operator code).
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_set_value" takes node as Integer, value as Integer:
    Set node.value to value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends a child to a node's ordered children list. Order matters because
many AST consumers rely on positional meaning (e.g. an If node's first
child is the condition, the second is the then-block).
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_add_child" takes node as Integer, child as Integer:
    proc list_append from ListCore with node.children, child
End Process

@Reasoning:
Accessor for the node type tag. Encapsulates field layout so consumers do
not depend on the struct offset.
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_node_type" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return node.node_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Accessor for the node payload value. Type interpretation (string vs integer
operator code) is the consumer's responsibility based on node_type.
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_node_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return node.value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the children-list pointer directly. Consumers that want random
access or iteration can read the list with ListCore primitives instead of
going through ast_node_child for every index.
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_node_children" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return node.children
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the count of children for the node. Used by traversal code to bound
the iteration index.
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_node_child_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc list_length from ListCore with node.children
End Process

@Reasoning:
Indexed child access. Out-of-range index is a caller error; consumers
expecting a specific positional child (e.g. If condition at index 0) rely
on having validated the child count first.
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_node_child" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc list_get from ListCore with node.children, index
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TOKEN HANDLING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Shifts the two lookahead slots one position forward: current <- peek, peek
<- lexer.next. Preserves the LL(2) invariant after every consumption.
@End Reasoning
Process called "advance" takes parser as Integer:
    Set parser.current_token to parser.peek_token
    Set parser.peek_token to proc matlab_lexer_next_token from Lexer with parser.lexer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Convenience getter for the current token's type tag — most parser predicates
need only the type, not the value or position.
@End Reasoning
Process called "current_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc matlab_token_type from Lexer with parser.current_token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Asserts the current token is the expected type, consumes it, and returns
the token. Returns 0 on mismatch — callers treat 0 as a parse error and
typically synthesize an error AST node. No exception/throw semantics; the
zero-return is the only error channel.
@End Reasoning
Process called "expect" takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to expected_type:
        Let token be parser.current_token
        proc advance with parser
        Return token
    End If

    Note: Error - unexpected token
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Non-consuming type predicate returning 1/0. Used by parse_postfix to peek
for '(' / '[' / '{' / '.' / "'" / ".'" before deciding which postfix form
(call, indexing, field access, transpose) to dispatch.
@End Reasoning
Process called "match" takes parser as Integer, token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Let current be proc current_type with parser
    If current is equal to token_type:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Consumes any run of NEWLINE tokens at the current position. MATLAB uses
newlines as statement separators (along with semicolons and commas in some
contexts) so block-level loops call skip_newlines before each statement to
tolerate blank lines without trying to parse them.
@End Reasoning
Process called "skip_newlines" takes parser as Integer:
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_NEWLINE:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Return
        End If
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
At statement boundaries MATLAB treats newline, semicolon and comma all as
statement separators (semicolon additionally suppresses command-window echo,
which carries no syntactic weight in translation). The statement-list loops
call this to consume any run of those separators so a bare ';' or ',' after
a statement does not stall the parser on a token parse_primary cannot
advance over. It is kept distinct from skip_newlines because skip_newlines
is also invoked mid-expression, where consuming ';'/',' is incorrect.
@End Reasoning
Process called "skip_statement_separators" takes parser as Integer:
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_NEWLINE:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON:
                proc advance with parser
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
                    proc advance with parser
                Otherwise:
                    Return
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PROGRAM PARSING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry. MATLAB source files come in three shapes: function files
(begin with "function"), class files (begin with "classdef"), and script
files (anything else). This routine sniffs the first non-newline token to
dispatch — function files may contain multiple top-level function
declarations and are looped; class and script files have exactly one
top-level unit.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_program" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let program be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_PROGRAM

    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Determine if script or function file
    Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_FUNCTION:
        Note: Function file - parse function definitions
        While token_type is not equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_FUNCTION:
                Let func be proc parse_function with parser
                proc ast_add_child with program, func
            End If

            proc skip_newlines with parser
            Set token_type to proc current_type with parser
        End While
    Otherwise:
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_CLASSDEF:
            Note: Class file - parse class definition
            Let class_def be proc parse_classdef with parser
            proc ast_add_child with program, class_def
        Otherwise:
            Note: Script file - parse statements
            Let script be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_SCRIPT
            proc parse_statement_list with parser, script
            proc ast_add_child with program, script
        End If
    End If

    Return program
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION PARSING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses one full MATLAB function: "function [outs] = name(ins) ... end".
Output-parameter parsing handles three forms — bracketed multi-output
"[a,b] = foo()", single output "y = foo()", and no-output "foo()" — by
looking at the post-'function' tokens. When a single identifier is followed
by '=' it is treated as an output; otherwise it is the function name. Input
parameters in (...) follow, then the body is parsed via
parse_statement_list_until_end which consumes through the matching "end".
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_function" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let func be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_FUNCTION

    Note: Expect 'function' keyword
    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_FUNCTION
    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Parse output parameters [out1, out2] or single output
    Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_LBRACKET:
        Note: Multiple outputs
        proc advance with parser
        proc skip_newlines with parser

        Let outputs be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
        proc ast_set_value with outputs, "outputs"

        Let outputs_done be 0
        While outputs_done is equal to 0:
            Set token_type to proc current_type with parser
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
                Let output be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
                Let output_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
                Let output_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with output_token
                proc ast_set_value with output, output_name
                proc ast_add_child with outputs, output
            End If

            proc skip_newlines with parser
            Set token_type to proc current_type with parser

            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
                proc advance with parser
                proc skip_newlines with parser
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_RBRACKET:
                    proc advance with parser
                    proc skip_newlines with parser
                    proc ast_add_child with func, outputs
                    Note: Expect '='
                    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_ASSIGN
                    proc skip_newlines with parser
                    Set outputs_done to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Unexpected token in output list - stop output parsing
                    proc ast_add_child with func, outputs
                    Set outputs_done to 1
                End If
            End If
        End While
    Otherwise:
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
            Note: Single output or just function name
            Set output to proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
            Set output_token to proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
            Set output_name to proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with output_token
            proc ast_set_value with output, output_name

            proc skip_newlines with parser
            Set token_type to proc current_type with parser

            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_ASSIGN:
                Note: This was an output parameter
                proc advance with parser
                proc skip_newlines with parser
                proc ast_add_child with func, output
            Otherwise:
                Note: This was the function name, no output
                proc ast_set_value with func, output_name
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Parse function name
    Set token_type to proc current_type with parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        Let name_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
        Let func_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with name_token

        Note: Only set name if not already set
        Let current_name be proc ast_node_value with func
        Let name_len be proc string_length from StringCore with current_name
        If name_len is equal to 0:
            proc ast_set_value with func, func_name
        End If
    End If

    Note: Parse input parameters
    proc skip_newlines with parser
    Set token_type to proc current_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
        proc advance with parser
        proc skip_newlines with parser

        Let inputs be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
        proc ast_set_value with inputs, "inputs"

        Let inputs_done be 0
        While inputs_done is equal to 0:
            Set token_type to proc current_type with parser
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
                Let input be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
                Let input_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
                Let input_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with input_token
                proc ast_set_value with input, input_name
                proc ast_add_child with inputs, input
            End If

            proc skip_newlines with parser
            Set token_type to proc current_type with parser

            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
                proc advance with parser
                proc skip_newlines with parser
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_RPAREN:
                    proc advance with parser
                    proc skip_newlines with parser
                    proc ast_add_child with func, inputs
                    Set inputs_done to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Unexpected token in input list - stop input parsing
                    proc ast_add_child with func, inputs
                    Set inputs_done to 1
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Note: Parse function body
    proc skip_newlines with parser
    Let body be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_SCRIPT
    proc parse_statement_list_until_end with parser, body
    proc ast_add_child with func, body

    Note: Expect 'end' keyword
    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_END
    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Return func
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CLASS PARSING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses "classdef Name < Base ... end" headers, captures the optional single-
base-class via "<", and then iterates over the class body blocks
(properties / methods / events / enumeration), dispatching each into its
own parser. Terminates on the matching "end".
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_classdef" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let class_def be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_CLASSDEF

    Note: Expect 'classdef' keyword
    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_CLASSDEF
    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Parse class name
    Let name_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
    Let class_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with name_token
    proc ast_set_value with class_def, class_name

    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Check for base class
    Let token_type be proc current_type with parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_LESS_THAN:
        proc advance with parser
        proc skip_newlines with parser

        Let base_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
        Let base_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with base_token
        Let base be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
        proc ast_set_value with base, base_name
        proc ast_add_child with class_def, base
    End If

    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Parse class body (properties, methods, events, enumeration)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Set token_type to proc current_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_PROPERTIES:
            Let props be proc parse_properties with parser
            proc ast_add_child with class_def, props
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_METHODS:
                Let methods be proc parse_methods with parser
                proc ast_add_child with class_def, methods
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EVENTS:
                    Let events be proc parse_events with parser
                    proc ast_add_child with class_def, events
                Otherwise:
                    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_ENUMERATION:
                        Let enums be proc parse_enumeration with parser
                        proc ast_add_child with class_def, enums
                    Otherwise:
                        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_END:
                            proc advance with parser
                            Return class_def
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Unexpected token
                            Return class_def
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        proc skip_newlines with parser
    End While

    Return class_def
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a "properties ... end" block inside a classdef. Each property is
emitted as an MATLAB_IDENTIFIER child carrying its name, which is the payload
the HIR field model and the MATLAB backend consume; attribute brackets and
type/default specifications are not part of the property-name contract and
are skipped at this level.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_properties" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let props be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_PROPERTIES

    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_PROPERTIES
    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Parse property declarations until 'end'
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
            Let prop be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
            Let prop_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
            Let prop_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with prop_token
            proc ast_set_value with prop, prop_name
            proc ast_add_child with props, prop
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_END:
                proc advance with parser
                Return props
            Otherwise:
                proc skip_newlines with parser
            End If
        End If

        proc skip_newlines with parser
    End While

    Return props
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a "methods ... end" block. Each method definition is parsed via the
same parse_function used at top level — methods are syntactically identical
to free functions; their classdef containment is captured at the AST
parent level.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_methods" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let methods be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_METHODS

    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_METHODS
    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Parse method definitions until 'end'
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_FUNCTION:
            Let method be proc parse_function with parser
            proc ast_add_child with methods, method
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_END:
                proc advance with parser
                Return methods
            Otherwise:
                proc skip_newlines with parser
            End If
        End If

        proc skip_newlines with parser
    End While

    Return methods
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses an "events ... end" block — MATLAB's class event-declaration syntax.
Each event becomes an IDENTIFIER child; semantic information about event
attributes is left for a future pass.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_events" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let events be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_EVENTS

    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_EVENTS
    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Parse event names until 'end'
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
            Let event be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
            Let event_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
            Let event_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with event_token
            proc ast_set_value with event, event_name
            proc ast_add_child with events, event
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_END:
                proc advance with parser
                Return events
            Otherwise:
                proc skip_newlines with parser
            End If
        End If

        proc skip_newlines with parser
    End While

    Return events
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses an "enumeration ... end" block (MATLAB class enumeration). Each
enumerator becomes an IDENTIFIER child. The optional underlying-value
expression after an enumerator name is not parsed here for the same scope-
limit reason as parse_properties.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_enumeration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let enums be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_ENUMERATION

    proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_ENUMERATION
    proc skip_newlines with parser

    Note: Parse enumeration values until 'end'
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
            Let enum_val be proc create_ast_node with MATLAB_IDENTIFIER
            Let enum_token be proc expect with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER
            Let enum_name be proc matlab_token_value from Lexer with enum_token
            proc ast_set_value with enum_val, enum_name
            proc ast_add_child with enums, enum_val
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_END:
                proc advance with parser
                Return enums
            Otherwise:
                proc skip_newlines with parser
            End If
        End If

        proc skip_newlines with parser
    End While

    Return enums
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATEMENT PARSING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Drives statement-by-statement parsing until EOF. Adds each successfully
parsed statement to the container's children. Used by the top-level script
parser; the function-body variant uses parse_statement_list_until_end which
stops at "end" instead.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_statement_list" takes parser as Integer, container as Integer:
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        proc skip_statement_separators with parser
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

        Note: Check for end of file
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            Return
        Otherwise:
            Note: Parse statement
            Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
            If stmt is not equal to 0:
                proc ast_add_child with container, stmt
            End If
        End If
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Variant of parse_statement_list that stops on the "end" keyword (not EOF).
Used to parse function bodies and any control-flow block body that
terminates at the matching "end". The terminating "end" is NOT consumed
here — the caller (parse_function, parse_if_statement, etc.) consumes it
explicitly so it can detect missing closers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_statement_list_until_end" takes parser as Integer, container as Integer:
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        proc skip_statement_separators with parser
        Let token_type be proc current_type with parser

        Note: Check for 'end' keyword
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_END:
            Return
        Otherwise:
            Note: Stop at EOF to avoid a non-terminating loop on unclosed blocks
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EOF:
                Return
            Otherwise:
                Note: Parse statement
                Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
                If stmt is not equal to 0:
                    proc ast_add_child with container, stmt
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Statement-level dispatch. Recognizes control-flow openers (if/for/parfor/
spmd/while/switch/try) and routes to their dedicated parsers; jump
statements (return/break/continue) emit zero-child marker nodes since they
need no payload; global/persistent declarations route to specialized
parsers; anything else falls through to parse_assignment_or_expr_statement
